HEADWORD: Undertone
<hw>Un"der*tone`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A low or subdued
tone or utterance; a tone less loud than usual.</def> <-- 2. an
attitude, usu. conveyed by more than one part of an action or a
communication, but not explicitly expressed. -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

